<Link id="l00188" /><CodeLine lineNumber="188"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// The file modification time as reported from the underlying file system.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00189" /><CodeLine lineNumber="189"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00190" /><CodeLine lineNumber="190"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// The returned value allows for nanosecond precision but the actual</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00192" /><CodeLine lineNumber="192"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// There is no guarantee for what kind of resolution you can expect, the</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00781" /><CodeLine lineNumber="781"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Create a potentially unique file name but does not create it.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00782" /><CodeLine lineNumber="782"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00783" /><CodeLine lineNumber="783"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Generates a unique path suitable for a temporary file but does not</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00784" /><CodeLine lineNumber="784"><Highlight kind="comment">/// open or create the file. The name is based on \\a Model with &#39;%&#39;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00785" /><CodeLine lineNumber="785"><Highlight kind="comment">/// replaced by a random char in &#91;0-9a-f&#93;. If \\a MakeAbsolute is true</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00786" /><CodeLine lineNumber="786"><Highlight kind="comment">/// then the system&#39;s temp directory is prepended first. If \\a MakeAbsolute</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00787" /><CodeLine lineNumber="787"><Highlight kind="comment">/// is false the current directory will be used instead.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00788" /><CodeLine lineNumber="788"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00789" /><CodeLine lineNumber="789"><Highlight kind="comment">/// This function does not check if the file exists. If you want to be sure</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00790" /><CodeLine lineNumber="790"><Highlight kind="comment">/// that the file does not yet exist, you should use enough &#39;%&#39; characters</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00791" /><CodeLine lineNumber="791"><Highlight kind="comment">/// in your model to ensure this. Each &#39;%&#39; gives 4-bits of entropy so you can</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00792" /><CodeLine lineNumber="792"><Highlight kind="comment">/// use 32 of them to get 128 bits of entropy.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00793" /><CodeLine lineNumber="793"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00794" /><CodeLine lineNumber="794"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Example: clang-%%-%%-%%-%%-%%.s =&gt; clang-a0-b1-c2-d3-e4.s</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00795" /><CodeLine lineNumber="795"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00796" /><CodeLine lineNumber="796"><Highlight kind="comment">/// @param Model Name to base unique path off of.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00797" /><CodeLine lineNumber="797"><Highlight kind="comment">/// @param ResultPath Set to the file&#39;s path.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00798" /><CodeLine lineNumber="798"><Highlight kind="comment">/// @param MakeAbsolute Whether to use the system temp directory.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00799" /><CodeLine lineNumber="799"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">void</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/sys/fs/#aa37537b95a42a73ea04d8dd2803378da">createUniquePath</a>(</Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/twine">Twine</a> &amp;Model, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallvectorimpl">SmallVectorImpl&lt;char&gt;</a> &amp;ResultPath,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00800" /><CodeLine lineNumber="800"><Highlight kind="normal">                      </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">bool</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> MakeAbsolute);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00801" /><CodeLine lineNumber="801"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00802" /><CodeLine lineNumber="802"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Create a uniquely named file.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00803" /><CodeLine lineNumber="803"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00804" /><CodeLine lineNumber="804"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Generates a unique path suitable for a temporary file and then opens it as a</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00805" /><CodeLine lineNumber="805"><Highlight kind="comment">/// file. The name is based on \\a Model with &#39;%&#39; replaced by a random char in</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00806" /><CodeLine lineNumber="806"><Highlight kind="comment">/// &#91;0-9a-f&#93;. If \\a Model is not an absolute path, the temporary file will be</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00807" /><CodeLine lineNumber="807"><Highlight kind="comment">/// created in the current directory.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00808" /><CodeLine lineNumber="808"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00809" /><CodeLine lineNumber="809"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Example: clang-%%-%%-%%-%%-%%.s =&gt; clang-a0-b1-c2-d3-e4.s</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00810" /><CodeLine lineNumber="810"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00811" /><CodeLine lineNumber="811"><Highlight kind="comment">/// This is an atomic operation. Either the file is created and opened, or the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00812" /><CodeLine lineNumber="812"><Highlight kind="comment">/// file system is left untouched.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00813" /><CodeLine lineNumber="813"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00816" /><CodeLine lineNumber="816"><Highlight kind="comment">/// be first created as foo-abc123.o and then renamed.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00817" /><CodeLine lineNumber="817"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00820" /><CodeLine lineNumber="820"><Highlight kind="comment">/// @param ResultPath Set to the opened file&#39;s absolute path.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00821" /><CodeLine lineNumber="821"><Highlight kind="comment">/// @param Flags Set to the opened file&#39;s flags.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00822" /><CodeLine lineNumber="822"><Highlight kind="comment">/// @param Mode Set to the opened file&#39;s permissions.</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00824" /><CodeLine lineNumber="824"><Highlight kind="comment">///          otherwise a platform-specific error&#95;code.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01163" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1163"><Highlight kind="comment">/// &lt;em&gt;errc::success&lt;/em&gt;, the file is locked by the calling process. Until the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01164" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1164"><Highlight kind="comment">/// process unlocks the file by calling \\a unlockFile, all attempts to lock the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01165" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1165"><Highlight kind="comment">/// same file will fail/block. The process that locked the file may assume that</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01166" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1166"><Highlight kind="comment">/// none of other processes read or write this file, provided that all processes</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01167" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1167"><Highlight kind="comment">/// lock the file prior to accessing its content.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01168" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1168"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01169" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1169"><Highlight kind="comment">/// @param FD      The descriptor representing the file to lock.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01170" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1170"><Highlight kind="comment">/// @param Timeout Time in milliseconds that the process should wait before</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01171" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1171"><Highlight kind="comment">///                reporting lock failure. Zero value means try to get lock only</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01172" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1172"><Highlight kind="comment">///                once.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01173" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1173"><Highlight kind="comment">/// @returns errc::success if lock is successfully obtained,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01174" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1174"><Highlight kind="comment">/// errc::no&#95;lock&#95;available if the file cannot be locked, or platform-specific</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01175" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1175"><Highlight kind="comment">/// error&#95;code otherwise.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01176" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1176"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01177" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1177"><Highlight kind="comment">/// @note Care should be taken when using this function in a multithreaded</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01178" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1178"><Highlight kind="comment">/// context, as it may not prevent other threads in the same process from</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01179" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1179"><Highlight kind="comment">/// obtaining a lock on the same file, even if they are using a different file</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01180" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1180"><Highlight kind="comment">/// descriptor.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01181" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1181"><Highlight kind="normal">std::error&#95;code</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01182" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1182" lineLink="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/sys/fs/#a2b8ef26c55540747c5f83d0cd898fe92"><Highlight kind="normal"><a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/sys/fs/#a2b8ef26c55540747c5f83d0cd898fe92">tryLockFile</a>(</Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">int</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> FD,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01183" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1183"><Highlight kind="normal">            std::chrono::milliseconds Timeout = std::chrono::milliseconds(0));</Highlight></CodeLine>
